#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn85"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn85:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 85 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 85 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn85:0.2"
msgid "Bodhirājakumārasutta "
msgstr "With Prince Bodhi "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli2.91, sc1
msgctxt "mn85:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn85:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane migadāye. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Bhaggas on Crocodile Hill, in the deer park at Bhesakaḷā’s Wood. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
#. VAR: kokanado → kokanudo (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bodhissa rājakumārassa kokanado nāma pāsādo acirakārito hoti anajjhāvuṭṭho samaṇena vā brāhmaṇena vā kenaci vā manussabhūtena. "
msgstr "Now at that time a new stilt longhouse named Pink Lotus had recently been constructed for Prince Bodhi. It had not yet been occupied by an ascetic or brahmin or any person at all. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya3
msgctxt "mn85:3.1"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro sañjikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "Then Prince Bodhi addressed the brahmin student Sañjikāputta, "

msgctxt "mn85:3.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā mama vacanena bhagavato pāde sirasā vanda, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ puccha: "
msgstr "“Please, dear Sañjikāputta, go to the Buddha, and in my name bow with your head to his feet. Ask him if he is healthy and well, nimble, strong, and living comfortably. "

msgctxt "mn85:3.3"
msgid "‘bodhi, bhante, rājakumāro bhagavato pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchatī’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:3.4"
msgid "Evañca vadehi: "
msgstr "And then ask him whether he "

msgctxt "mn85:3.5"
msgid "‘adhivāsetu kira, bhante, bhagavā bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’”ti. "
msgstr "might accept tomorrow’s meal from me together with the mendicant Saṅgha.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya4
msgctxt "mn85:4.1"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavatā saddhiṃ sammodi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Sañjikāputta replied. He did as Prince Bodhi asked, and "

msgctxt "mn85:4.2"
msgid "Sammodanīyaṃ kathaṃ sāraṇīyaṃ vītisāretvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

#. VAR: bodhi kho → bodhi bho gotama (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:4.3"
msgid "“bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.4"
msgid "Evañca vadeti: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.5"
msgid "‘adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghenā’”ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.6"
msgid "Adhivāsesi bhagavā tuṇhībhāvena. "
msgstr "the Buddha consented in silence. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.92, sc2
msgctxt "mn85:4.7"
msgid "Atha kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bhagavato adhivāsanaṃ viditvā uṭṭhāyāsanā yena bodhi rājakumāro tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then, knowing that the Buddha had consented, Sañjikāputta got up from his seat, went to Prince Bodhi, and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:4.8"
msgid "“avocumha bhoto vacanena taṃ bhavantaṃ gotamaṃ: "
msgstr "“I gave the ascetic Gotama your message, "

msgctxt "mn85:4.9"
msgid "‘bodhi kho rājakumāro bhoto gotamassa pāde sirasā vandati, appābādhaṃ appātaṅkaṃ lahuṭṭhānaṃ balaṃ phāsuvihāraṃ pucchati. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.10"
msgid "Evañca vadeti—"
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.11"
msgid "adhivāsetu kira bhavaṃ gotamo bodhissa rājakumārassa svātanāya bhattaṃ saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṅghenā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:4.12"
msgid "Adhivuṭṭhañca pana samaṇena gotamenā”ti. "
msgstr "and he accepted.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, sc3
msgctxt "mn85:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro tassā rattiyā accayena sake nivesane paṇītaṃ khādanīyaṃ bhojanīyaṃ paṭiyādāpetvā, kokanadañca pāsādaṃ odātehi dussehi santharāpetvā yāva pacchimasopānakaḷevarā, sañjikāputtaṃ māṇavaṃ āmantesi: "
msgstr "And when the night had passed Prince Bodhi had a variety of delicious foods prepared in his own home. He also had the Pink Lotus longhouse spread with white cloth down to the last step of the staircase. Then he said to Sañjikāputta, "

msgctxt "mn85:5.2"
msgid "“ehi tvaṃ, samma sañjikāputta, yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkama; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocehi: "
msgstr "“Please, dear Sañjikāputta, go to the Buddha, and announce the time, saying, "

msgctxt "mn85:5.3"
msgid "‘kālo, bhante, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, it’s time. The meal is ready.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:5.4"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bho”ti kho sañjikāputto māṇavo bodhissa rājakumārassa paṭissutvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavato kālaṃ ārocesi: "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Sañjikāputta replied, and he did as he was asked. "

msgctxt "mn85:5.5"
msgid "“kālo, bho gotama, niṭṭhitaṃ bhattan”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc4
msgctxt "mn85:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pubbaṇhasamayaṃ nivāsetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena bodhissa rājakumārassa nivesanaṃ tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha robed up in the morning and, taking his bowl and robe, went to Prince Bodhi’s home. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya7
msgctxt "mn85:7.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bodhi rājakumāro bahidvārakoṭṭhake ṭhito hoti bhagavantaṃ āgamayamāno. "
msgstr "Now at that time Prince Bodhi was standing outside the gates waiting for the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn85:7.2"
msgid "Addasā kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "Seeing the Buddha coming off in the distance, "

msgctxt "mn85:7.3"
msgid "Disvāna paccuggantvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā purakkhatvā yena kokanado pāsādo tenupasaṅkami. "
msgstr "he went out to greet him. After bowing and inviting the Buddha to go first, he approached the Pink Lotus longhouse. "

msgctxt "mn85:7.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā pacchimaṃ sopānakaḷevaraṃ nissāya aṭṭhāsi. "
msgstr "But the Buddha stopped by the last step of the staircase. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:7.5"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then Prince Bodhi said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:7.6"
msgid "“abhiruhatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, abhiruhatu sugato dussāni; "
msgstr "“Sir, let the Blessed One ascend on the cloth! Let the Holy One ascend on the cloth! "

msgctxt "mn85:7.7"
msgid "yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.” "

msgctxt "mn85:7.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bhagavā tuṇhī ahosi. "
msgstr "But when he said this, the Buddha kept silent. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:7.9"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho … pe … "
msgstr "For a second time … "

msgctxt "mn85:7.10"
msgid "tatiyampi kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and a third time, Prince Bodhi said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:7.11"
msgid "“abhiruhatu, bhante, bhagavā dussāni, abhiruhatu sugato dussāni; "
msgstr "“Sir, let the Blessed One ascend on the cloth! Let the Holy One ascend on the cloth! "

msgctxt "mn85:7.12"
msgid "yaṃ mama assa dīgharattaṃ hitāya sukhāyā”ti. "
msgstr "It will be for my lasting welfare and happiness.” "

# NOTE: What a beautiful expression of the intimacy and understanding they shared!
#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli2.93, sc5
msgctxt "mn85:7.13"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā āyasmantaṃ ānandaṃ apalokesi. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha glanced at Venerable Ānanda. "

msgctxt "mn85:7.14"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā ānando bodhiṃ rājakumāraṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "So Ānanda said to Prince Bodhi, "

msgctxt "mn85:7.15"
msgid "“saṃharatu, rājakumāra, dussāni; "
msgstr "“Fold up the cloth, Prince. "

#. VAR: celapaṭikaṃ → celapattikaṃ (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:7.16"
msgid "na bhagavā celapaṭikaṃ akkamissati. "
msgstr "The Buddha will not step upon white cloth. "

#. VAR: anukampatī”ti → apaloketīti (sabbattha)
msgctxt "mn85:7.17"
msgid "Pacchimaṃ janataṃ tathāgato anukampatī”ti. "
msgstr "The Realized One has compassion for future generations.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya8
msgctxt "mn85:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro dussāni saṃharāpetvā uparikokanadapāsāde āsanāni paññapesi. "
msgstr "So Prince Bodhi had the cloth folded up and the seats spread out upstairs in the longhouse. "

msgctxt "mn85:8.2"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā kokanadaṃ pāsādaṃ abhiruhitvā paññatte āsane nisīdi saddhiṃ bhikkhusaṃghena. "
msgstr "Then the Buddha ascended the longhouse and sat on the seats spread out together with the Saṅgha of mendicants. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya9
msgctxt "mn85:9.1"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro buddhappamukhaṃ bhikkhusaṃghaṃ paṇītena khādanīyena bhojanīyena sahatthā santappesi sampavāresi. "
msgstr "Then Prince Bodhi served and satisfied the mendicant Saṅgha headed by the Buddha with his own hands with a variety of delicious foods. "

msgctxt "mn85:9.2"
msgid "Atha kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ bhuttāviṃ onītapattapāṇiṃ aññataraṃ nīcaṃ āsanaṃ gahetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. "
msgstr "When the Buddha had eaten and washed his hand and bowl, Prince Bodhi took a low seat, sat to one side, "

msgctxt "mn85:9.3"
msgid "Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:9.4"
msgid "“mayhaṃ kho, bhante, evaṃ hoti: "
msgstr "“Sir, this is what I think: "

msgctxt "mn85:9.5"
msgid "‘na kho sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabban’”ti. "
msgstr "‘Pleasure is not gained through pleasure; pleasure is gained through pain.’” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya10, sc6
msgctxt "mn85:10.1"
msgid "“Mayhampi kho, rājakumāra, pubbeva sambodhā anabhisambuddhassa bodhisattasseva sato etadahosi: "
msgstr "“Prince, before my awakening—when I was still unawakened but intent on awakening—I too thought: "

msgctxt "mn85:10.2"
msgid "‘na kho sukhena sukhaṃ adhigantabbaṃ, dukkhena kho sukhaṃ adhigantabban’ti. "
msgstr "‘Pleasure is not gained through pleasure; pleasure is gained through pain.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya11
msgctxt "mn85:11.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, aparena samayena daharova samāno susukāḷakeso bhadrena yobbanena samannāgato paṭhamena vayasā akāmakānaṃ mātāpitūnaṃ assumukhānaṃ rudantānaṃ kesamassuṃ ohāretvā kāsāyāni vatthāni acchādetvā agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajiṃ. "
msgstr "Some time later, while still black-haired, blessed with youth, in the prime of life—though my mother and father wished otherwise, weeping with tearful faces—I shaved off my hair and beard, dressed in ocher robes, and went forth from the lay life to homelessness. "

msgctxt "mn85:11.2"
msgid "So evaṃ pabbajito samāno kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "Once I had gone forth I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:11.3"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso kālāma, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend Kālāma, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:11.4"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Āḷāra Kālāma replied, "

msgctxt "mn85:11.5"
msgid "‘viharatāyasmā, "
msgstr "‘Stay, venerable. "

msgctxt "mn85:11.6"
msgid "tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:11.7"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ. "
msgstr "I quickly memorized that teaching. "

msgctxt "mn85:11.8"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi passāmīti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca. "
msgstr "So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others. "

msgctxt "mn85:11.9"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:11.10"
msgid "‘na kho āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti; "
msgstr "‘It is not solely by mere faith that Āḷāra Kālāma declares: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.” "

msgctxt "mn85:11.11"
msgid "addhā āḷāro kālāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ viharatī’ti. "
msgstr "Surely he meditates knowing and seeing this teaching.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya12, sc7
msgctxt "mn85:12.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him, "

#. VAR: upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti → upasampajja pavedesīti (s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:12.2"
msgid "‘kittāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Kālāma, to what extent do you say you’ve realized this teaching with your own insight?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:12.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo ākiñcaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi. "
msgstr "When I said this, he declared the dimension of nothingness. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.5"
msgid "‘na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā; "
msgstr "‘It’s not just Āḷāra Kālāma who has faith, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.6"
msgid "na kho āḷārasseva kālāmassa atthi vīriyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "energy, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.7"
msgid "sati … "
msgstr "mindfulness, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.8"
msgid "samādhi … "
msgstr "immersion, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.9"
msgid "paññā, mayhampatthi paññā. "
msgstr "and wisdom; I too have these things. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.10"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ āḷāro kālāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Āḷāra Kālāma says he has realized with his own insight?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:12.11"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ. "
msgstr "I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.12"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena āḷāro kālāmo tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā āḷāraṃ kālāmaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I approached Āḷāra Kālāma and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.13"
msgid "‘ettāvatā no, āvuso kālāma, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Kālāma, have you realized this teaching with your own insight up to this point, and declare having achieved it?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.14"
msgid "‘Ettāvatā kho ahaṃ, āvuso, imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I have, reverend.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.15"
msgid "‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.16"
msgid "‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, "
msgstr "‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "mn85:12.17"
msgid "ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma. "
msgstr "to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions! "

msgctxt "mn85:12.18"
msgid "Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi, taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi. "
msgstr "So the teaching that I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it, you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.19"
msgid "Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi, tamahaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedemi. "
msgstr "The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, I’ve realized with my own insight, and declare having achieved it. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.20"
msgid "Iti yāhaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi tamahaṃ dhammaṃ jānāmi. "
msgstr "So the teaching that I know, you know, and the teaching you know, I know. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.21"
msgid "Iti yādiso ahaṃ, tādiso tuvaṃ; yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso ahaṃ. "
msgstr "I am like you and you are like me. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.22"
msgid "Ehi dāni, āvuso, ubhova santā imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharāmā’ti. "
msgstr "Come now, reverend! We should both lead this community together.’ "

#. VAR: attano → idaṃ padaṃ bj, s1-3, km, pts1 potthakesu
#. VAR: attanā → attano (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:12.23"
msgid "Iti kho, rājakumāra, āḷāro kālāmo ācariyo me samāno attano antevāsiṃ maṃ samānaṃ attanā samasamaṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi. "
msgstr "And that is how my teacher Āḷāra Kālāma placed me, his student, on the same position as him, and honored me with lofty praise. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.24"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.25"
msgid "‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva ākiñcaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of nothingness.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:12.26"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ. "
msgstr "Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#. VAR: udako → uddako (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:12.27"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him, "

#. VAR: āvuso → āvuso rāma (bj, s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:12.28"
msgid "‘icchāmahaṃ, āvuso, imasmiṃ dhammavinaye brahmacariyaṃ caritun’ti. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, I wish to live the spiritual life in this teaching and training.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.29"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Uddaka replied, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.30"
msgid "‘viharatāyasmā, "
msgstr "‘Stay, venerable. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.31"
msgid "tādiso ayaṃ dhammo yattha viññū puriso nacirasseva sakaṃ ācariyakaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā’ti. "
msgstr "This teaching is such that a sensible person can soon realize their own teacher’s doctrine with their own insight and live having achieved it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.32"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ pariyāpuṇiṃ. "
msgstr "I quickly memorized that teaching. "

msgctxt "mn85:12.33"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tāvatakeneva oṭṭhapahatamattena lapitalāpanamattena ñāṇavādañca vadāmi, theravādañca jānāmi passāmīti ca paṭijānāmi, ahañceva aññe ca. "
msgstr "So far as lip-recital and oral recitation were concerned, I spoke with knowledge and the authority of the elders. I claimed to know and see, and so did others. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:12.34"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:12.35"
msgid "‘na kho rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ kevalaṃ saddhāmattakena sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesi; "
msgstr "‘It is not solely by mere faith that Rāma declared: “I realize this teaching with my own insight, and live having achieved it.” "

msgctxt "mn85:12.36"
msgid "addhā rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ jānaṃ passaṃ vihāsī’ti. "
msgstr "Surely he meditated knowing and seeing this teaching.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya13, sc9
msgctxt "mn85:13.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.2"
msgid "‘kittāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedesī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, to what extent did Rāma say he’d realized this teaching with his own insight?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:13.3"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto nevasaññānāsaññāyatanaṃ pavedesi. "
msgstr "When I said this, Uddaka, son of Rāma, declared the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:13.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.5"
msgid "‘na kho rāmasseva ahosi saddhā, mayhampatthi saddhā; "
msgstr "‘It’s not just Rāma who had faith, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.6"
msgid "na kho rāmasseva ahosi vīriyaṃ … pe … "
msgstr "energy, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.7"
msgid "sati … "
msgstr "mindfulness, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.8"
msgid "samādhi … "
msgstr "immersion, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.9"
msgid "paññā, mayhampatthi paññā. "
msgstr "and wisdom; I too have these things. "

msgctxt "mn85:13.10"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmīti pavedeti tassa dhammassa sacchikiriyāya padaheyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I make an effort to realize the same teaching that Rāma said he had realized with his own insight?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:13.11"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, nacirasseva khippameva taṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihāsiṃ. "
msgstr "I quickly realized that teaching with my own insight, and lived having achieved it. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc10
#. VAR: udako rāmaputto → uddako rāmaputto (bj, s1-3)
msgctxt "mn85:13.12"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, yena udako rāmaputto tenupasaṅkamiṃ; upasaṅkamitvā udakaṃ rāmaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I approached Uddaka, son of Rāma, and said to him, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.13"
msgid "‘ettāvatā no, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend, had Rāma realized this teaching with his own insight up to this point, and declared having achieved it?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:13.14"
msgid "‘Ettāvatā kho, āvuso, rāmo imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesī’ti. "
msgstr "‘He had, reverend.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:13.15"
msgid "‘Ahampi kho, āvuso, ettāvatā imaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharāmī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I too have realized this teaching with my own insight up to this point, and live having achieved it.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:13.16"
msgid "‘Lābhā no, āvuso, suladdhaṃ no, āvuso, "
msgstr "‘We are fortunate, reverend, so very fortunate "

msgctxt "mn85:13.17"
msgid "ye mayaṃ āyasmantaṃ tādisaṃ sabrahmacāriṃ passāma. "
msgstr "to see a venerable such as yourself as one of our spiritual companions! "

msgctxt "mn85:13.18"
msgid "Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi. "
msgstr "So the teaching that Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it, you've realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it. "

msgctxt "mn85:13.19"
msgid "Yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharasi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja pavedesi. "
msgstr "The teaching that you’ve realized with your own insight, and live having achieved it, Rāma had realized with his own insight, and declared having achieved it. "

msgctxt "mn85:13.20"
msgid "Iti yaṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi taṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi; yaṃ tvaṃ dhammaṃ jānāsi taṃ dhammaṃ rāmo abhiññāsi. "
msgstr "So the teaching that Rāma directly knew, you know, and the teaching you know, Rāma directly knew. "

msgctxt "mn85:13.21"
msgid "Iti yādiso rāmo ahosi tādiso tuvaṃ, yādiso tuvaṃ tādiso rāmo ahosi. "
msgstr "Rāma was like you and you are like Rāma. "

msgctxt "mn85:13.22"
msgid "Ehi dāni, āvuso, tuvaṃ imaṃ gaṇaṃ pariharā’ti. "
msgstr "Come now, reverend! You should lead this community.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:13.23"
msgid "Iti kho, rājakumāra, udako rāmaputto sabrahmacārī me samāno ācariyaṭṭhāne maṃ ṭhapesi, uḷārāya ca maṃ pūjāya pūjesi. "
msgstr "And that is how my spiritual companion Uddaka, son of Rāma, placed me in the position of a teacher, and honored me with lofty praise. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:13.24"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:13.25"
msgid "‘nāyaṃ dhammo nibbidāya na virāgāya na nirodhāya na upasamāya na abhiññāya na sambodhāya na nibbānāya saṃvattati, yāvadeva nevasaññānāsaññāyatanūpapattiyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This teaching doesn’t lead to disillusionment, dispassion, cessation, peace, insight, awakening, and extinguishment. It only leads as far as rebirth in the dimension of neither perception nor non-perception.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:13.26"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, taṃ dhammaṃ analaṅkaritvā tasmā dhammā nibbijja apakkamiṃ. "
msgstr "Realizing that this teaching was inadequate, I left disappointed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya14, sc11
msgctxt "mn85:14.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, kiṃkusalagavesī anuttaraṃ santivarapadaṃ pariyesamāno, magadhesu anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno, yena uruvelā senānigamo tadavasariṃ. "
msgstr "I set out to discover what is skillful, seeking the supreme state of sublime peace. Traveling stage by stage in the Magadhan lands, I arrived at Senanigama near Uruvelā. "

#. VAR: samantā → sāmantā (?)
msgctxt "mn85:14.2"
msgid "Tatthaddasaṃ ramaṇīyaṃ bhūmibhāgaṃ, pāsādikañca vanasaṇḍaṃ, nadiñca sandantiṃ setakaṃ supatitthaṃ, ramaṇīyaṃ samantā ca gocaragāmaṃ. "
msgstr "There I saw a delightful park, a lovely grove with a flowing river that was clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby was a village to go for alms. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:14.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:14.4"
msgid "‘ramaṇīyo vata bho bhūmibhāgo, pāsādiko ca vanasaṇḍo, nadī ca sandati setakā supatitthā, ramaṇīyā samantā ca gocaragāmo. "
msgstr "‘This park is truly delightful, a lovely grove with a flowing river that’s clean and charming, with smooth banks. And nearby there’s a village to go for alms. "

msgctxt "mn85:14.5"
msgid "Alaṃ vatidaṃ kulaputtassa padhānatthikassa padhānāyā’ti. "
msgstr "This is good enough for a gentleman who wishes to put forth effort in meditation.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:14.6"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tattheva nisīdiṃ: "
msgstr "So I sat down right there, thinking, "

msgctxt "mn85:14.7"
msgid "‘alamidaṃ padhānāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘This is good enough for meditation.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya15
msgctxt "mn85:15.1"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "And then these three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya16, sc12
msgctxt "mn85:16.1"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying in water. "

msgctxt "mn85:16.2"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya: "
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking "

msgctxt "mn85:16.3"
msgid "‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "to light a fire and produce heat. "

msgctxt "mn85:16.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, Prince? "

#. VAR: abhimanthento → abhimatthanto (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:16.5"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ udake nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log lying in water, could they light a fire and produce heat?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "mn85:16.6"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“No, sir. "

msgctxt "mn85:16.7"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn85:16.8"
msgid "Aduñhi, bhante, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ tañca pana udake nikkhittaṃ, "
msgstr "Because it’s a green, sappy log, and it’s lying in the water. "

msgctxt "mn85:16.9"
msgid "yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti. "
msgstr "That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya17, sc14
msgctxt "mn85:17.1"
msgid "“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi avūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho. "
msgstr "“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who don’t live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. They haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening. "

msgctxt "mn85:17.2"
msgid "Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:17.3"
msgid "No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:17.4"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, paṭhamā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "This was the first example that occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya18, sc15
msgctxt "mn85:18.1"
msgid "Aparāpi kho maṃ, rājakumāra, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "Then a second example occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "mn85:18.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a green, sappy log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water. "

msgctxt "mn85:18.3"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya: "
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking "

msgctxt "mn85:18.4"
msgid "‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "to light a fire and produce heat. "

msgctxt "mn85:18.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, Prince? "

msgctxt "mn85:18.6"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "By drilling the stick against that green, sappy log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "mn85:18.7"
msgid "“No hidaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“No, sir. "

msgctxt "mn85:18.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn85:18.9"
msgid "Aduñhi, bhante, allaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ sasnehaṃ kiñcāpi ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ, "
msgstr "Because it’s still a green, sappy log, despite the fact that it’s lying on dry land far from water. "

msgctxt "mn85:18.10"
msgid "yāvadeva ca pana so puriso kilamathassa vighātassa bhāgī assā”ti. "
msgstr "That person will eventually get weary and frustrated.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc18
msgctxt "mn85:18.11"
msgid "“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ na suppahīno hoti, na suppaṭippassaddho. "
msgstr "“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. But they haven’t internally given up or stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are incapable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening. "

msgctxt "mn85:18.12"
msgid "Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:18.13"
msgid "No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, abhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:18.14"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, dutiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "This was the second example that occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya19, sc19
msgctxt "mn85:19.1"
msgid "Aparāpi kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "Then a third example occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
msgctxt "mn85:19.2"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ. "
msgstr "Suppose there was a dried up, withered log, and it was lying on dry land far from the water. "

msgctxt "mn85:19.3"
msgid "Atha puriso āgaccheyya uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya: "
msgstr "Then a person comes along with a drill-stick, thinking "

msgctxt "mn85:19.4"
msgid "‘aggiṃ abhinibbattessāmi, tejo pātukarissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "to light a fire and produce heat. "

msgctxt "mn85:19.5"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, Prince? "

msgctxt "mn85:19.6"
msgid "api nu so puriso amuṃ sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ ārakā udakā thale nikkhittaṃ uttarāraṇiṃ ādāya abhimanthento aggiṃ abhinibbatteyya, tejo pātukareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "By drilling the stick against that dried up, withered log on dry land far from water, could they light a fire and produce heat?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "mn85:19.7"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir. "

msgctxt "mn85:19.8"
msgid "Taṃ kissa hetu? "
msgstr "Why is that? "

msgctxt "mn85:19.9"
msgid "Aduñhi, bhante, sukkhaṃ kaṭṭhaṃ koḷāpaṃ, tañca pana ārakā udakā thale nikkhittan”ti. "
msgstr "Because it’s a dried up, withered log, and it’s lying on dry land far from water.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:19.10"
msgid "“Evameva kho, rājakumāra, ye hi keci samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā kāyena ceva cittena ca kāmehi vūpakaṭṭhā viharanti, yo ca nesaṃ kāmesu kāmacchando kāmasneho kāmamucchā kāmapipāsā kāmapariḷāho so ca ajjhattaṃ suppahīno hoti suppaṭippassaddho. "
msgstr "“In the same way, there are ascetics and brahmins who live withdrawn in body and mind from sensual pleasures. And they have internally given up and stilled desire, affection, infatuation, thirst, and passion for sensual pleasures. Regardless of whether or not they feel painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings because of their efforts, they are capable of knowledge and vision, of supreme awakening. "

msgctxt "mn85:19.11"
msgid "Opakkamikā cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:19.12"
msgid "No cepi te bhonto samaṇabrāhmaṇā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, bhabbāva te ñāṇāya dassanāya anuttarāya sambodhāya. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:19.13"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tatiyā upamā paṭibhāsi anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "This was the third example that occurred to me. "

msgctxt "mn85:19.14"
msgid "Imā kho maṃ, rājakumāra, tisso upamā paṭibhaṃsu anacchariyā pubbe assutapubbā. "
msgstr "These are the three examples, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, that occurred to me. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya20, sc22
msgctxt "mn85:20.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:20.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇheyyaṃ abhinippīḷeyyaṃ abhisantāpeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:20.3"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhāmi abhinippīḷemi abhisantāpemi. "
msgstr "So that’s what I did, "

msgctxt "mn85:20.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti. "
msgstr "until sweat ran from my armpits. "

msgctxt "mn85:20.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, rājakumāra, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gahetvā khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya; "
msgstr "It was like when a strong man grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them. "

msgctxt "mn85:20.6"
msgid "evameva kho me, rājakumāra, dantebhidantamādhāya, jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca, cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato kacchehi sedā muccanti. "
msgstr "In the same way, with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of my mouth, I squeezed, squashed, and tortured mind with mind until sweat ran from my armpits. "

msgctxt "mn85:20.7"
msgid "Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato. "
msgstr "My energy was roused up and unflagging, and my mindfulness was established and lucid, but my body was disturbed, not tranquil, because I’d pushed too hard with that painful striving. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya21, sc23
msgctxt "mn85:21.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:21.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ appāṇakaṃyeva jhānaṃ jhāyeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I practice the breathless absorption?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:21.3"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāse uparundhiṃ. "
msgstr "So I cut off my breathing through my mouth and nose. "

msgctxt "mn85:21.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti. "
msgstr "But then winds came out my ears making a loud noise, "

msgctxt "mn85:21.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma kammāragaggariyā dhamamānāya adhimatto saddo hoti; "
msgstr "like the puffing of a blacksmith’s bellows. "

msgctxt "mn85:21.6"
msgid "evameva kho me, rājakumāra, mukhato ca nāsato ca assāsapassāsesu uparuddhesu kaṇṇasotehi vātānaṃ nikkhamantānaṃ adhimatto saddo hoti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:21.7"
msgid "Āraddhaṃ kho pana me, rājakumāra, vīriyaṃ hoti asallīnaṃ, upaṭṭhitā sati asammuṭṭhā, sāraddho ca pana me kāyo hoti appaṭippassaddho, teneva dukkhappadhānena padhānābhitunnassa sato. "
