#. REF: nya26, sc28
msgctxt "mn85:26.1"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā disvā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Then some deities saw me and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:26.2"
msgid "‘kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama is dead.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:26.3"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Others said, "

msgctxt "mn85:26.4"
msgid "‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, api ca kālaṃ karotī’ti. "
msgstr "‘He’s not dead, but he’s dying.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:26.5"
msgid "Ekaccā devatā evamāhaṃsu: "
msgstr "Others said, "

#. VAR: arahato evarūpo hotī’ti → vihārotveveso arahato ti
#. VAR: Vihāro tveva so → vihārotveveso (bj)
msgctxt "mn85:26.6"
msgid "‘na kālaṅkato samaṇo gotamo, nāpi kālaṃ karoti. Arahaṃ samaṇo gotamo. Vihāro tveva so arahato evarūpo hotī’ti. "
msgstr "‘He’s not dead or dying. The ascetic Gotama is a perfected one, for that is how the perfected ones live.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya27, sc29
msgctxt "mn85:27.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:27.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjeyyan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I practice completely cutting off food?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:27.3"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But deities came to me and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:27.4"
msgid "‘mā kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajji. "
msgstr "‘Good sir, don’t practice totally cutting off food. "

#. VAR: ajjhohāressāma → ajjhoharissāma (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:27.5"
msgid "Sace kho tvaṃ, mārisa, sabbaso āhārupacchedāya paṭipajjissasi, tassa te mayaṃ dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāressāma, tāya tvaṃ yāpessasī’ti. "
msgstr "If you do, we’ll infuse divine nectar into your pores and you will live on that.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:27.6"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

#. VAR: ajajjitaṃ → ajaddhukaṃ (bj, s2, s3, km, pts1) | ajjukaṃ (s1)
#. VAR: ajjhohāreyyuṃ → ajjhohareyyuṃ (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:27.7"
msgid "‘ahañceva kho pana sabbaso ajajjitaṃ paṭijāneyyaṃ. Imā ca me devatā dibbaṃ ojaṃ lomakūpehi ajjhohāreyyuṃ, tāya cāhaṃ yāpeyyaṃ, taṃ mamassa musā’ti. "
msgstr "‘If I claim to be completely fasting while these deities are infusing divine nectar in my pores, that would be a lie on my part.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:27.8"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, tā devatā paccācikkhāmi. ‘Halan’ti vadāmi. "
msgstr "So I dismissed those deities, saying, ‘There’s no need.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya28, sc30
msgctxt "mn85:28.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:28.2"
msgid "‘yannūnāhaṃ thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsan’ti. "
msgstr "‘Why don’t I just take a little bit of food each time, a cup of broth made from mung beans, lentils, chickpeas, or green gram.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:28.3"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ. "
msgstr "So that’s what I did, "

msgctxt "mn85:28.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, thokaṃ thokaṃ āhāraṃ āhārayato pasataṃ pasataṃ, yadi vā muggayūsaṃ yadi vā kulatthayūsaṃ yadi vā kaḷāyayūsaṃ yadi vā hareṇukayūsaṃ, adhimattakasimānaṃ patto kāyo hoti. "
msgstr "until my body became extremely emaciated. "

msgctxt "mn85:28.5"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma āsītikapabbāni vā kāḷapabbāni vā; evamevassu me aṅgapaccaṅgāni bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, my limbs became like the joints of an eighty-year-old or a corpse, "

msgctxt "mn85:28.6"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma oṭṭhapadaṃ; evamevassu me ānisadaṃ hoti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "my bottom became like a camel’s hoof, "

msgctxt "mn85:28.7"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma vaṭṭanāvaḷī; evamevassu me piṭṭhikaṇṭako uṇṇatāvanato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "my vertebrae stuck out like beads on a string, "

msgctxt "mn85:28.8"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma jarasālāya gopānasiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti; evamevassu me phāsuḷiyo oluggaviluggā bhavanti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "and my ribs were as gaunt as the broken-down rafters on an old barn. "

msgctxt "mn85:28.9"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma gambhīre udapāne udakatārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti; evamevassu me akkhikūpesu akkhitārakā gambhīragatā okkhāyikā dissanti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, the gleam of my eyes sank deep in their sockets, like the gleam of water sunk deep down a well. "

#. VAR: samphuṭito → saṃpuṭito (bj, mr) | saṃphusito (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn85:28.10"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma tittakālābu āmakacchinno vātātapena samphuṭito hoti sammilāto; evamevassu me sīsacchavi samphuṭitā hoti sammilātā tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, my scalp shriveled and withered like a green bitter-gourd in the wind and sun. "

msgctxt "mn85:28.11"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, ‘udaracchaviṃ parimasissāmī’ti piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi, ‘piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ parimasissāmī’ti udaracchaviṃyeva pariggaṇhāmi. Yāvassu me, rājakumāra, udaracchavi piṭṭhikaṇṭakaṃ allīnā hoti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, the skin of my belly stuck to my backbone, so that when I tried to rub the skin of my belly I grabbed my backbone, and when I tried to rub my backbone I rubbed the skin of my belly. "

msgctxt "mn85:28.12"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, ‘vaccaṃ vā muttaṃ vā karissāmī’ti tattheva avakujjo papatāmi tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, when I tried to urinate or defecate I fell face down right there. "

msgctxt "mn85:28.13"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, imameva kāyaṃ assāsento pāṇinā gattāni anumajjāmi. Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, pāṇinā gattāni anumajjato pūtimūlāni lomāni kāyasmā papatanti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "Due to eating so little, when I tried to relieve my body by rubbing my limbs with my hands, the hair, rotted at its roots, fell out. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya29
msgctxt "mn85:29.1"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, manussā disvā evamāhaṃsu: ‘kāḷo samaṇo gotamo’ti, "
msgstr "Then some people saw me and said, ‘The ascetic Gotama is black.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:29.2"
msgid "ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, sāmo samaṇo gotamo’ti. "
msgstr "Some said, ‘He’s not black, he’s brown.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:29.3"
msgid "Ekacce manussā evamāhaṃsu: ‘na kāḷo samaṇo gotamo, napi sāmo, maṅguracchavi samaṇo gotamo’ti. "
msgstr "Some said, ‘He’s neither black nor brown. The ascetic Gotama has tawny skin.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:29.4"
msgid "Yāvassu me, rājakumāra, tāva parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto upahato hoti tāyevappāhāratāya. "
msgstr "That’s how far the pure, bright complexion of my skin had been ruined by taking so little food. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya30, sc31
msgctxt "mn85:30.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

#. VAR: tibbā → tippā (bj, s1-3, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:30.2"
msgid "‘ye kho keci atītamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayiṃsu, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo. "
msgstr "‘Whatever ascetics and brahmins have experienced painful, sharp, severe, acute feelings due to overexertion—whether in the past, future, or present—this is as far as it goes, no-one has done more than this. "

msgctxt "mn85:30.3"
msgid "Yepi hi keci anāgatamaddhānaṃ samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayissanti, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:30.4"
msgid "Yepi hi keci etarahi samaṇā vā brāhmaṇā vā opakkamikā dukkhā tibbā kharā kaṭukā vedanā vedayanti, etāvaparamaṃ nayito bhiyyo. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:30.5"
msgid "Na kho panāhaṃ imāya kaṭukāya dukkarakārikāya adhigacchāmi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; "
msgstr "But I have not achieved any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones by this severe, gruelling work. "

msgctxt "mn85:30.6"
msgid "siyā nu kho añño maggo bodhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "Could there be another path to awakening?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya31
msgctxt "mn85:31.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:31.2"
msgid "‘abhijānāmi kho panāhaṃ pitu sakkassa kammante sītāya jambucchāyāya nisinno vivicceva kāmehi vivicca akusalehi dhammehi savitakkaṃ savicāraṃ vivekajaṃ pītisukhaṃ paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja viharitā; "
msgstr "‘I recall sitting in the cool shade of the rose-apple tree while my father the Sakyan was off working. Quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption, which has the rapture and bliss born of seclusion, while placing the mind and keeping it connected. "

msgctxt "mn85:31.3"
msgid "siyā nu kho eso maggo bodhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "Could that be the path to awakening?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:31.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, satānusāri viññāṇaṃ ahosi: "
msgstr "Stemming from that memory came the realization: "

msgctxt "mn85:31.5"
msgid "‘eseva maggo bodhāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘*That* is the path to awakening!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya32
msgctxt "mn85:32.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:32.2"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti? "
msgstr "‘Why am I afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:32.3"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:32.4"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ tassa sukhassa bhāyāmi yaṃ taṃ sukhaṃ aññatreva kāmehi aññatra akusalehi dhammehī’ti. "
msgstr "‘I’m not afraid of that pleasure, for it has nothing to do with sensual pleasures or unskillful qualities.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya33, sc32
msgctxt "mn85:33.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:33.2"
msgid "‘na kho taṃ sukaraṃ sukhaṃ adhigantuṃ evaṃ adhimattakasimānaṃ pattakāyena. Yannūnāhaṃ oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāreyyaṃ odanakummāsan’ti. "
msgstr "‘I can’t achieve that pleasure with a body so excessively emaciated. Why don’t I eat some solid food, some rice and porridge?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:33.3"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ. "
msgstr "So I ate some solid food. "

msgctxt "mn85:33.4"
msgid "Tena kho pana maṃ, rājakumāra, samayena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū paccupaṭṭhitā honti: "
msgstr "Now at that time the five mendicants were attending on me, thinking, "

msgctxt "mn85:33.5"
msgid "‘yaṃ kho samaṇo gotamo dhammaṃ adhigamissati taṃ no ārocessatī’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama will tell us of any truth that he realizes.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:33.6"
msgid "Yato kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāresiṃ odanakummāsaṃ, atha me te pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nibbijja pakkamiṃsu: "
msgstr "But when I ate some solid food, they left disappointed in me, saying, "

#. VAR: bāhulliko → bāhuliko (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:33.7"
msgid "‘bāhulliko samaṇo gotamo padhānavibbhanto, āvatto bāhullāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘The ascetic Gotama has become indulgent; he has strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya34-37, sc33
msgctxt "mn85:34-37.1"
msgid "So kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, oḷārikaṃ āhāraṃ āhāretvā balaṃ gahetvā vivicceva kāmehi … pe … paṭhamaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ. "
msgstr "After eating solid food and gathering my strength, quite secluded from sensual pleasures, secluded from unskillful qualities, I entered and remained in the first absorption … "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.2"
msgid "Vitakkavicārānaṃ vūpasamā … dutiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "second absorption … "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.3"
msgid "tatiyaṃ jhānaṃ … "
msgstr "third absorption … "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.4"
msgid "catutthaṃ jhānaṃ upasampajja vihāsiṃ. "
msgstr "fourth absorption. "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.5"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte pubbenivāsānussatiñāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ. "
msgstr "When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward recollection of past lives. "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.6"
msgid "So anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarāmi. "
msgstr "I recollected many past lives. That is: one, two, three, four, five, ten, twenty, thirty, forty, fifty, a hundred, a thousand, a hundred thousand rebirths; many eons of the world contracting, many eons of the world expanding, many eons of the world contracting and expanding. And so I recollected my many kinds of past lives, with features and details. "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.7"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā paṭhame yāme paṭhamā "
msgstr "This was the first knowledge, which I achieved in the first watch of the night. "

msgctxt "mn85:34-37.8"
msgid "vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato. "
msgstr "Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya38, sc34
msgctxt "mn85:38.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte sattānaṃ cutūpapātañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ. "
msgstr "When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the death and rebirth of sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn85:38.2"
msgid "So dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena satte passāmi cavamāne upapajjamāne hīne paṇīte suvaṇṇe dubbaṇṇe sugate duggate yathākammūpage satte pajānāmi … pe … "
msgstr "With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman, I saw sentient beings passing away and being reborn—inferior and superior, beautiful and ugly, in a good place or a bad place. I understood how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya39
msgctxt "mn85:39.1"
msgid "ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā majjhime yāme dutiyā vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato. "
msgstr "This was the second knowledge, which I achieved in the middle watch of the night. Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya40, sc35
msgctxt "mn85:40.1"
msgid "So evaṃ samāhite citte parisuddhe pariyodāte anaṅgaṇe vigatūpakkilese mudubhūte kammaniye ṭhite āneñjappatte āsavānaṃ khayañāṇāya cittaṃ abhininnāmesiṃ. "
msgstr "When my mind had immersed in samādhi like this—purified, bright, flawless, rid of corruptions, pliable, workable, steady, and imperturbable—I extended it toward knowledge of the ending of defilements. "

msgctxt "mn85:40.2"
msgid "So ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ … pe … ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ; "
msgstr "I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’. "

msgctxt "mn85:40.3"
msgid "‘ime āsavā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ … pe … ‘ayaṃ āsavanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "I truly understood: ‘These are defilements’ … ‘This is the origin of defilements’ … ‘This is the cessation of defilements’ … ‘This is the practice that leads to the cessation of defilements’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya41
msgctxt "mn85:41.1"
msgid "Tassa me evaṃ jānato evaṃ passato kāmāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, bhavāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha, avijjāsavāpi cittaṃ vimuccittha. "
msgstr "Knowing and seeing like this, my mind was freed from the defilements of sensuality, desire to be reborn, and ignorance. "

msgctxt "mn85:41.2"
msgid "Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ ahosi. "
msgstr "When it was freed, I knew it was freed. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:41.3"
msgid "‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti abbhaññāsiṃ. "
msgstr "I understood: ‘Rebirth is ended; the spiritual journey has been completed; what had to be done has been done; there is no return to any state of existence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya42
msgctxt "mn85:42.1"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho me, rājakumāra, rattiyā pacchime yāme tatiyā "
msgstr "This was the third knowledge, which I achieved in the last watch of the night. "

msgctxt "mn85:42.2"
msgid "vijjā adhigatā, avijjā vihatā, vijjā uppannā; tamo vihato, āloko uppanno—yathā taṃ appamattassa ātāpino pahitattassa viharato. "
msgstr "Ignorance was destroyed and knowledge arose; darkness was destroyed and light arose, as happens for a meditator who is diligent, keen, and resolute. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya43, sc36
msgctxt "mn85:43.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:43.2"
msgid "‘adhigato kho myāyaṃ dhammo gambhīro duddaso duranubodho santo paṇīto atakkāvacaro nipuṇo paṇḍitavedanīyo. "
msgstr "‘This principle I have discovered is deep, hard to see, hard to understand, peaceful, sublime, beyond the scope of reason, subtle, comprehensible to the astute. "

msgctxt "mn85:43.3"
msgid "Ālayarāmā kho panāyaṃ pajā ālayaratā ālayasammuditā. "
msgstr "But people like attachment, they love it and enjoy it. "

msgctxt "mn85:43.4"
msgid "Ālayarāmāya kho pana pajāya ālayaratāya ālayasammuditāya duddasaṃ idaṃ ṭhānaṃ yadidaṃ—idappaccayatāpaṭiccasamuppādo. "
msgstr "It’s hard for them to see this thing; that is, specific conditionality, dependent origination. "

msgctxt "mn85:43.5"
msgid "Idampi kho ṭhānaṃ duddasaṃ—yadidaṃ sabbasaṅkhārasamatho sabbūpadhipaṭinissaggo taṇhākkhayo virāgo nirodho nibbānaṃ. "
msgstr "It’s also hard for them to see this thing; that is, the stilling of all activities, the letting go of all attachments, the ending of craving, fading away, cessation, extinguishment. "

msgctxt "mn85:43.6"
msgid "Ahañceva kho pana dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ, pare ca me na ājāneyyuṃ, so mamassa kilamatho, sā mamassa vihesā’ti. "
msgstr "And if I were to teach the Dhamma, others might not understand me, which would be wearying and troublesome for me.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:43.7"
msgid "Apissu maṃ, rājakumāra, imā anacchariyā gāthāyo paṭibhaṃsu pubbe assutapubbā: "
msgstr "And then these verses, which were neither supernaturally inspired, nor learned before in the past, occurred to me: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc37
msgctxt "mn85:43.8"
msgid "‘Kicchena me adhigataṃ, "
msgstr "‘I’ve struggled hard to realize this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:43.9"
msgid "halaṃ dāni pakāsituṃ; "
msgstr "enough with trying to explain it! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:43.10"
msgid "Rāgadosaparetehi, "
msgstr "This teaching is not easily understood "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:43.11"
msgid "nāyaṃ dhammo susambudho. "
msgstr "by those mired in greed and hate. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc38
msgctxt "mn85:43.12"
msgid "Paṭisotagāmiṃ nipuṇaṃ, "
msgstr "Those caught up in greed can’t see "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:43.13"
msgid "gambhīraṃ duddasaṃ aṇuṃ; "
msgstr "what’s subtle, going against the stream, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:43.14"
msgid "Rāgarattā na dakkhanti, "
msgstr "deep, hard to see, and very fine, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: āvuṭā → āvaṭā (bj, pts1) | āvutā (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn85:43.15"
msgid "tamokhandhena āvuṭā’ti. "
msgstr "for they’re shrouded in a mass of darkness.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc39
msgctxt "mn85:43.16"
msgid "Itiha me, rājakumāra, paṭisañcikkhato appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati no dhammadesanāya. "
msgstr "And as I reflected like this, my mind inclined to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya44, sc40
msgctxt "mn85:44.1"
msgid "Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmuno sahampatissa mama cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing what I was thinking, thought, "

#. VAR: namati → namissati (?)
msgctxt "mn85:44.2"
msgid "‘nassati vata bho loko; vinassati vata bho loko. Yatra hi nāma tathāgatassa arahato sammāsambuddhassa appossukkatāya cittaṃ namati no dhammadesanāyā’ti. "
msgstr "‘Oh my goodness! The world will be lost, the world will perish! For the mind of the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha, inclines to remaining passive, not to teaching the Dhamma.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:44.3"
msgid "Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā bāhaṃ pasāreyya pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—brahmaloke antarahito mama purato pāturahosi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati, as easily as a strong person would extend or contract their arm, vanished from the Brahmā realm and reappeared in front of the Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn85:44.4"
msgid "Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati ekaṃsaṃ uttarāsaṅgaṃ karitvā yenāhaṃ tenañjaliṃ paṇāmetvā maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "He arranged his robe over one shoulder, knelt on his right knee, raised his joined palms toward the Buddha, and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:44.5"
msgid "‘desetu, bhante, bhagavā dhammaṃ, desetu sugato dhammaṃ. "
msgstr "‘Sir, let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! Let the Holy One teach the Dhamma! "

msgctxt "mn85:44.6"
msgid "Santi sattā apparajakkhajātikā assavanatāya dhammassa parihāyanti; "
msgstr "There are beings with little dust in their eyes. They’re in decline because they haven’t heard the teaching. "

msgctxt "mn85:44.7"
msgid "bhavissanti dhammassa aññātāro’ti. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand the teaching!’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:44.8"
msgid "Idamavoca, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati; "
msgstr "That’s what Brahmā Sahampati said. "

msgctxt "mn85:44.9"
msgid "idaṃ vatvā athāparaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then he went on to say: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc41
msgctxt "mn85:44.10"
msgid "‘Pāturahosi magadhesu pubbe, "
msgstr "‘Among the Magadhans there appeared in the past "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.11"
msgid "Dhammo asuddho samalehi cintito; "
msgstr "an impure teaching thought up by those still stained. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Apāpuretaṃ → avāpuretaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "mn85:44.12"
msgid "Apāpuretaṃ amatassa dvāraṃ, "
msgstr "Fling open the door to the deathless! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.13"
msgid "Suṇantu dhammaṃ vimalenānubuddhaṃ. "
msgstr "Let them hear the teaching the immaculate one discovered. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc42
msgctxt "mn85:44.14"
msgid "Sele yathā pabbatamuddhaniṭṭhito, "
msgstr "Standing high on a rocky mountain, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.15"
msgid "Yathāpi passe janataṃ samantato; "
msgstr "you can see the people all around. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.16"
msgid "Tathūpamaṃ dhammamayaṃ sumedha, "
msgstr "In just the same way, all-seer, wise one, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.17"
msgid "Pāsādamāruyha samantacakkhu. "
msgstr "ascend the palace built of Dhamma! "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc43
#. VAR: Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ → sokāvakiṇṇaṃ (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn85:44.18"
msgid "Sokāvatiṇṇaṃ janatamapetasoko, "
msgstr "You’re free of sorrow; but look at these people "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.19"
msgid "Avekkhassu jātijarābhibhūtaṃ; "
msgstr "overwhelmed with sorrow, oppressed by rebirth and old age. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.20"
msgid "Uṭṭhehi vīra vijitasaṅgāma, "
msgstr "Rise, hero! Victor in battle, leader of the caravan, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: aṇaṇa → anaṇa (bj, s1-3, km, pts1, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:44.21"
msgid "Satthavāha aṇaṇa vicara loke; "
msgstr "wander the world without obligation. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Desassu → desessu (s1) | desetu (s2, s3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:44.22"
msgid "Desassu bhagavā dhammaṃ, "
msgstr "Let the Blessed One teach the Dhamma! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:44.23"
msgid "Aññātāro bhavissantī’ti. "
msgstr "There will be those who understand!’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: nya45, sc44
msgctxt "mn85:45.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, brahmuno ca ajjhesanaṃ viditvā sattesu ca kāruññataṃ paṭicca buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokesiṃ. "
msgstr "Then, understanding Brahmā’s invitation, I surveyed the world with the eye of a Buddha, because of my compassion for sentient beings. "

msgctxt "mn85:45.2"
msgid "Addasaṃ kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante. "
msgstr "And I saw sentient beings with little dust in their eyes, and some with much dust in their eyes; with keen faculties and with weak faculties, with good qualities and with bad qualities, easy to teach and hard to teach. And some of them lived seeing the danger in the fault to do with the next world, while others did not. "

#. VAR: ṭhitāni → tiṭṭhanti (bj, s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn85:45.3"
msgid "Seyyathāpi nāma uppaliniyaṃ vā paduminiyaṃ vā puṇḍarīkiniyaṃ vā appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni antonimuggaposīni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakānuggatāni samodakaṃ ṭhitāni, appekaccāni uppalāni vā padumāni vā puṇḍarīkāni vā udake jātāni udake saṃvaḍḍhāni udakā accuggamma ṭhitāni anupalittāni udakena; "
msgstr "It’s like a pool with blue water lilies, or pink or white lotuses. Some of them sprout and grow in the water without rising above it, thriving underwater. Some of them sprout and grow in the water reaching the water’s surface. And some of them sprout and grow in the water but rise up above the water and stand with no water clinging to them. "

msgctxt "mn85:45.4"
msgid "evameva kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra; buddhacakkhunā lokaṃ volokento addasaṃ satte apparajakkhe mahārajakkhe tikkhindriye mudindriye svākāre dvākāre suviññāpaye duviññāpaye, appekacce paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante, appekacce na paralokavajjabhayadassāvine viharante. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:45.5"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, brahmānaṃ sahampatiṃ gāthāya paccabhāsiṃ: "
msgstr "Then I replied in verse to Brahmā Sahampati: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc45
msgctxt "mn85:45.6"
msgid "‘Apārutā tesaṃ amatassa dvārā, "
msgstr "‘Flung open are the doors to the deathless! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:45.7"
msgid "Ye sotavanto pamuñcantu saddhaṃ; "
msgstr "Let those with ears to hear decide their faith. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:45.8"
msgid "Vihiṃsasaññī paguṇaṃ na bhāsiṃ, "
msgstr "Thinking it would be troublesome, Brahmā, I did not teach "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:45.9"
msgid "Dhammaṃ paṇītaṃ manujesu brahme’ti. "
msgstr "the sophisticated, sublime Dhamma among humans.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc46
msgctxt "mn85:45.10"
msgid "Atha kho, rājakumāra, brahmā sahampati ‘katāvakāso khomhi bhagavatā dhammadesanāyā’ti maṃ abhivādetvā padakkhiṇaṃ katvā tatthevantaradhāyi. "
msgstr "Then Brahmā Sahampati, knowing that his request for me to teach the Dhamma had been granted, bowed and respectfully circled me, keeping me on his right, before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya46, sc47
msgctxt "mn85:46.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:46.2"
msgid "‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Who should I teach first of all? "

msgctxt "mn85:46.3"
msgid "Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti? "
msgstr "Who will quickly understand the teaching?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:46.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:46.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho āḷāro kālāmo paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko. "
msgstr "‘That Āḷāra Kālāma is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes. "

msgctxt "mn85:46.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ āḷārassa kālāmassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ; "
msgstr "Why don’t I teach him first of all? "

msgctxt "mn85:46.7"
msgid "so imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti. "
msgstr "He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:46.8"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "But a deity came to me and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:46.9"
msgid "‘sattāhakālaṅkato, bhante, āḷāro kālāmo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:46.10"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "And knowledge and vision arose in me, "

msgctxt "mn85:46.11"
msgid "‘sattāhakālaṅkato āḷāro kālāmo’ti. "
msgstr "‘Āḷāra Kālāma passed away seven days ago.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:46.12"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:46.13"
msgid "‘mahājāniyo kho āḷāro kālāmo. "
msgstr "‘This is a great loss for Āḷāra Kālāma. "

msgctxt "mn85:46.14"
msgid "Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti. "
msgstr "If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya47, sc48
msgctxt "mn85:47.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:47.2"
msgid "‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Who should I teach first of all? "

msgctxt "mn85:47.3"
msgid "Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti? "
msgstr "Who will quickly understand the teaching?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:47.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:47.5"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho udako rāmaputto paṇḍito viyatto medhāvī dīgharattaṃ apparajakkhajātiko. "
msgstr "‘That Uddaka, son of Rāma, is astute, competent, clever, and has long had little dust in his eyes. "

msgctxt "mn85:47.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ udakassa rāmaputtassa paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ; "
msgstr "Why don’t I teach him first of all? "

msgctxt "mn85:47.7"
msgid "so imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti. "
msgstr "He’ll quickly understand the teaching.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:47.8"
msgid "Atha kho maṃ, rājakumāra, devatā upasaṅkamitvā etadavoca: "
msgstr "But a deity came to me and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:47.9"
msgid "‘abhidosakālaṅkato, bhante, udako rāmaputto’ti. "
msgstr "‘Sir, Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:47.10"
msgid "Ñāṇañca pana me dassanaṃ udapādi: "
msgstr "And knowledge and vision arose in me, "

msgctxt "mn85:47.11"
msgid "‘abhidosakālaṅkato udako rāmaputto’ti. "
msgstr "‘Uddaka, son of Rāma, passed away just last night.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:47.12"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:47.13"
msgid "‘mahājāniyo kho udako rāmaputto. "
msgstr "‘This is a great loss for Uddaka. "

msgctxt "mn85:47.14"
msgid "Sace hi so imaṃ dhammaṃ suṇeyya, khippameva ājāneyyā’ti. "
msgstr "If he had heard the teaching, he would have understood it quickly.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya48, sc49
msgctxt "mn85:48.1"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:48.2"
msgid "‘kassa nu kho ahaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyaṃ? "
msgstr "‘Who should I teach first of all? "

msgctxt "mn85:48.3"
msgid "Ko imaṃ dhammaṃ khippameva ājānissatī’ti? "
msgstr "Who will quickly understand the teaching?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:48.4"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:48.5"
msgid "‘bahukārā kho me pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū ye maṃ padhānapahitattaṃ upaṭṭhahiṃsu. "
msgstr "‘The group of five mendicants were very helpful to me. They looked after me during my time of resolute striving. "

msgctxt "mn85:48.6"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ pañcavaggiyānaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ paṭhamaṃ dhammaṃ deseyyan’ti. "
msgstr "Why don’t I teach them first of all?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:48.7"
msgid "Tassa mayhaṃ, rājakumāra, etadahosi: "
msgstr "Then it occurred to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:48.8"
msgid "‘kahaṃ nu kho etarahi pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū viharantī’ti. "
msgstr "‘Where are the group of five mendicants staying these days?’ "

msgctxt "mn85:48.9"
msgid "Addasaṃ khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena pañcavaggiye bhikkhū bārāṇasiyaṃ viharante isipatane migadāye. "
msgstr "With clairvoyance that is purified and superhuman I saw that the group of five mendicants were staying near Benares, in the deer park at Isipatana. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya49
msgctxt "mn85:49.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, uruvelāyaṃ yathābhirantaṃ viharitvā yena bārāṇasī tena cārikaṃ pakkamiṃ. "
msgstr "So, when I had stayed in Uruvelā as long as I wished, I set out for Benares. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc50
msgctxt "mn85:49.2"
msgid "Addasā kho maṃ, rājakumāra, upako ājīvako antarā ca gayaṃ antarā ca bodhiṃ addhānamaggappaṭipannaṃ. "
msgstr "While I was traveling along the road between Gaya and Bodhgaya, the <i>Ājīvaka</i> ascetic Upaka saw me "

msgctxt "mn85:49.3"
msgid "Disvāna maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "and said, "

msgctxt "mn85:49.4"
msgid "‘vippasannāni kho te, āvuso, indriyāni, parisuddho chavivaṇṇo pariyodāto. "
msgstr "‘Reverend, your faculties are so very clear, and your complexion is pure and bright. "

msgctxt "mn85:49.5"
msgid "Kaṃsi tvaṃ, āvuso, uddissa pabbajito? Ko vā te satthā? Kassa vā tvaṃ dhammaṃ rocesī’ti? "
msgstr "In whose name have you gone forth, reverend? Who is your Teacher? Whose teaching do you believe in?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:49.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, upakaṃ ājīvakaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsiṃ: "
msgstr "I replied to Upaka in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc51
msgctxt "mn85:49.7"
msgid "‘Sabbābhibhū sabbavidūhamasmi, "
msgstr "‘I am the champion, the knower of all, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.8"
msgid "Sabbesu dhammesu anūpalitto; "
msgstr "unsullied in the midst of all things. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.9"
msgid "Sabbañjaho taṇhākkhaye vimutto, "
msgstr "I’ve given up all, freed in the ending of craving. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.10"
msgid "Sayaṃ abhiññāya kamuddiseyyaṃ. "
msgstr "When I know for myself, who should I follow? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc52
msgctxt "mn85:49.11"
msgid "Na me ācariyo atthi, "
msgstr "I have no teacher. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.12"
msgid "sadiso me na vijjati; "
msgstr "There is no-one like me. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.13"
msgid "Sadevakasmiṃ lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "In the world with its gods, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.14"
msgid "natthi me paṭipuggalo. "
msgstr "I have no counterpart. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc53
msgctxt "mn85:49.15"
msgid "Ahañhi arahā loke, "
msgstr "For in this world, I am the perfected one; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.16"
msgid "ahaṃ satthā anuttaro; "
msgstr "I am the supreme Teacher. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.17"
msgid "Ekomhi sammāsambuddho, "
msgstr "I alone am fully awakened, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.18"
msgid "sītibhūtosmi nibbuto. "
msgstr "cooled, extinguished. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc54
msgctxt "mn85:49.19"
msgid "Dhammacakkaṃ pavattetuṃ, "
msgstr "I am going to the city of Kāsi "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.20"
msgid "Gacchāmi kāsinaṃ puraṃ; "
msgstr "to roll forth the Wheel of Dhamma. "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Andhībhūtasmiṃ → andhabhūtasmiṃ (bj, s1, pts1) | andhabhūtasmi (s2, s3)
msgctxt "mn85:49.21"
msgid "Andhībhūtasmiṃ lokasmiṃ, "
msgstr "In this world that is so blind, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: Āhañchaṃ → āhaññiṃ (s1-3, km, mr)
msgctxt "mn85:49.22"
msgid "Āhañchaṃ amatadundubhin’ti. "
msgstr "I’ll beat the deathless drum!’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc55
msgctxt "mn85:49.23"
msgid "‘Yathā kho tvaṃ, āvuso, paṭijānāsi arahasi anantajino’ti. "
msgstr "‘According to what you claim, reverend, you ought to be the Infinite Victor.’ "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc56
msgctxt "mn85:49.24"
msgid "‘Mādisā ve jinā honti, "
msgstr "‘The victors are those who, like me, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.25"
msgid "ye pattā āsavakkhayaṃ; "
msgstr "have reached the ending of defilements. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn85:49.26"
msgid "Jitā me pāpakā dhammā, "
msgstr "I have conquered bad qualities, Upaka—"

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: tasmāhamupaka → tasmāhaṃ upakā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:49.27"
msgid "tasmāhamupaka jino’ti. "
msgstr "that’s why I’m a victor.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc57
#. VAR: hupeyyapāvuso’ti → huveyya pāvusoti (bj, pts1) | huveyyāvusoti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "mn85:49.28"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, upako ājīvako ‘hupeyyapāvuso’ti vatvā sīsaṃ okampetvā ummaggaṃ gahetvā pakkāmi. "
msgstr "When I had spoken, Upaka said: ‘If you say so, reverend.’ Shaking his head, he took a wrong turn and left. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya50, sc58
#. VAR: upasaṅkamiṃ → upasaṅkamāmi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:50.1"
msgid "Atha khvāhaṃ, rājakumāra, anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena bārāṇasī isipatanaṃ migadāyo yena pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū tenupasaṅkamiṃ. "
msgstr "Traveling stage by stage, I arrived at Benares, and went to see the group of five mendicants in the deer park at Isipatana. "

msgctxt "mn85:50.2"
msgid "Addasaṃsu kho maṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū dūratova āgacchantaṃ. "
msgstr "The group of five mendicants saw me coming off in the distance "

msgctxt "mn85:50.3"
msgid "Disvāna aññamaññaṃ saṇṭhapesuṃ: "
msgstr "and stopped each other, saying, "

msgctxt "mn85:50.4"
msgid "‘ayaṃ kho, āvuso, samaṇo gotamo āgacchati bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya. "
msgstr "‘Here comes the ascetic Gotama. He’s so indulgent; he strayed from the struggle and returned to indulgence. "

msgctxt "mn85:50.5"
msgid "So neva abhivādetabbo, na paccuṭṭhātabbo, nāssa pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahetabbaṃ; "
msgstr "We shouldn’t bow to him or rise for him or receive his bowl and robe. "

msgctxt "mn85:50.6"
msgid "api ca kho āsanaṃ ṭhapetabbaṃ—sace so ākaṅkhissati nisīdissatī’ti. "
msgstr "But we can set out a seat; he can sit if he likes.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:50.7"
msgid "Yathā yathā kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū upasaṅkamiṃ tathā tathā pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū nāsakkhiṃsu sakāya katikāya saṇṭhātuṃ. "
msgstr "Yet as I drew closer, the group of five mendicants were unable to stop themselves as they had agreed. "

msgctxt "mn85:50.8"
msgid "Appekacce maṃ paccuggantvā pattacīvaraṃ paṭiggahesuṃ. Appekacce āsanaṃ paññapesuṃ. Appekacce pādodakaṃ upaṭṭhapesuṃ. "
msgstr "Some came out to greet me and receive my bowl and robe, some spread out a seat, while others set out water for washing my feet. "

msgctxt "mn85:50.9"
msgid "Api ca kho maṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaranti. "
msgstr "But they still addressed me by name and as ‘reverend’. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya51
msgctxt "mn85:51.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I said to them, "

#. VAR: samudācaratha → samudācarittha (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:51.2"
msgid "‘mā, bhikkhave, tathāgataṃ nāmena ca āvusovādena ca samudācaratha; "
msgstr "‘Mendicants, don’t address me by name and as “reverend”. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.3"
msgid "arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.4"
msgid "Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.5"
msgid "Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:51.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But they said to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:51.7"
msgid "‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Gotama, even by that conduct, that practice, that grueling work you did not achieve any superhuman distinction in knowledge and vision worthy of the noble ones. How could you have achieved such a state now that you’ve become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and fallen into indulgence?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:51.8"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I said to them, "

msgctxt "mn85:51.9"
msgid "‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko na padhānavibbhanto na āvatto bāhullāya. "
msgstr "‘The Realized One has not become indulgent, strayed from the struggle and fallen into indulgence. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.10"
msgid "Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.11"
msgid "Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma. "

msgctxt "mn85:51.12"
msgid "Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc59
msgctxt "mn85:51.13"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But for a second time they said to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:51.14"
msgid "‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Gotama … you’ve fallen into indulgence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:51.15"
msgid "Dutiyampi kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So for a second time I said to them, "

msgctxt "mn85:51.16"
msgid "‘na, bhikkhave, tathāgato bāhulliko na padhānavibbhanto na āvatto bāhullāya. "
msgstr "‘The Realized One has not become indulgent …’ "

msgctxt "mn85:51.17"
msgid "Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:51.18"
msgid "Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn85:51.19"
msgid "Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc60
msgctxt "mn85:51.20"
msgid "Tatiyampi kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū maṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "But for a third time they said to me, "

msgctxt "mn85:51.21"
msgid "‘tāyapi kho tvaṃ, āvuso gotama, iriyāya tāya paṭipadāya tāya dukkarakārikāya nājjhagamā uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesaṃ; kiṃ pana tvaṃ etarahi bāhulliko padhānavibbhanto āvatto bāhullāya adhigamissasi uttari manussadhammā alamariyañāṇadassanavisesan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Reverend Gotama … you’ve fallen into indulgence.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya52, sc61
msgctxt "mn85:52.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr "So I said to them, "

#. VAR: pabhāvitametan’ti → vab­bhāvi­ta­metanti (bj) | bhāsitametanti (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn85:52.2"
msgid "‘abhijānātha me no tumhe, bhikkhave, ito pubbe evarūpaṃ pabhāvitametan’ti? "
msgstr "‘Mendicants, have you ever known me to speak like this before?’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:52.3"
msgid "‘No hetaṃ, bhante’. "
msgstr "‘No, sir.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:52.4"
msgid "‘Arahaṃ, bhikkhave, tathāgato sammāsambuddho. "
msgstr "‘The Realized One is Perfected, a fully awakened Buddha. "

msgctxt "mn85:52.5"
msgid "Odahatha, bhikkhave, sotaṃ. Amatamadhigataṃ ahamanusāsāmi, ahaṃ dhammaṃ desemi. "
msgstr "Listen up, mendicants: I have achieved the Deathless! I shall instruct you, I will teach you the Dhamma. "

msgctxt "mn85:52.6"
msgid "Yathānusiṭṭhaṃ tathā paṭipajjamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja viharissathā’ti. "
msgstr "By practicing as instructed you will soon realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. You will live having achieved with your own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.’ "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya53, pts-vp-pli2.94, sc62
msgctxt "mn85:53.1"
msgid "Asakkhiṃ kho ahaṃ, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiye bhikkhū saññāpetuṃ. "
msgstr "I was able to persuade the group of five mendicants. "

msgctxt "mn85:53.2"
msgid "Dvepi sudaṃ, rājakumāra, bhikkhū ovadāmi. Tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti. "
msgstr "Then sometimes I advised two mendicants, while the other three went for alms. "

#. VAR: chabbaggiyā → chabbaggā (s1-3, km) | chabbaggo (pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:53.3"
msgid "Yaṃ tayo bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti, tena chabbaggiyā yāpema. "
msgstr "Then those three would feed all six of us with what they brought back. "

msgctxt "mn85:53.4"
msgid "Tayopi sudaṃ, rājakumāra, bhikkhū ovadāmi, dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caranti. "
msgstr "Sometimes I advised three mendicants, while the other two went for alms. "

msgctxt "mn85:53.5"
msgid "Yaṃ dve bhikkhū piṇḍāya caritvā āharanti tena chabbaggiyā yāpema. "
msgstr "Then those two would feed all six of us with what they brought back. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya54, sc63
msgctxt "mn85:54.1"
msgid "Atha kho, rājakumāra, pañcavaggiyā bhikkhū mayā evaṃ ovadiyamānā evaṃ anusāsiyamānā nacirasseva—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihariṃsū”ti. "
msgstr "As the group of five mendicants were being advised and instructed by me like this, they soon realized the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life. They lived having achieved with their own insight the goal for which gentlemen rightly go forth from the lay life to homelessness.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya55, sc64
msgctxt "mn85:55.1"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, bodhi rājakumāro bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "When he had spoken, Prince Bodhi said to the Buddha, "

#. VAR: vināyakaṃ → nāyakaṃ (?)
msgctxt "mn85:55.2"
msgid "“kīva cirena nu kho, bhante, bhikkhu tathāgataṃ vināyakaṃ labhamāno—yassatthāya kulaputtā sammadeva agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajanti, tadanuttaraṃ—brahmacariyapariyosānaṃ diṭṭheva dhamme sayaṃ abhiññā sacchikatvā upasampajja vihareyyā”ti? "
msgstr "“Sir, when a mendicant has the Realized One as trainer, how long would it take for them to realize the supreme end of the spiritual path in this very life?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc65
msgctxt "mn85:55.3"
msgid "“Tena hi, rājakumāra, taṃyevettha paṭipucchissāmi. Yathā te khameyya, tathā naṃ byākareyyāsi. "
msgstr "“Well then, prince, I’ll ask you about this in return, and you can answer as you like. "

msgctxt "mn85:55.4"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, prince? "

#. VAR: aṅkusagayhe → aṅkusagaṇhe (s1-3, km)
#. VAR: hatthārūḷhe → hatthāruyhe (bj) | haṭṭhārūyhe (pts1)
msgctxt "mn85:55.5"
msgid "kusalo tvaṃ hatthārūḷhe aṅkusagayhe sippe”ti? "
msgstr "Are you skilled in the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:55.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante, kusalo ahaṃ hatthārūḷhe aṅkusagayhe sippe”ti. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya56, sc66
msgctxt "mn85:56.1"
msgid "“Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "“What do you think, prince? "

msgctxt "mn85:56.2"
msgid "idha puriso āgaccheyya: "
msgstr "Suppose a man were to come along thinking, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.3"
msgid "‘bodhi rājakumāro hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ jānāti; "
msgstr "‘Prince Bodhi knows the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.4"
msgid "tassāhaṃ santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkhissāmī’ti. "
msgstr "I’ll train in that art under him.’ "

msgctxt "mn85:56.5"
msgid "So cassa assaddho; "
msgstr "If he’s faithless, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.6"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ saddhena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya. "
msgstr "he wouldn’t achieve what he could with faith. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.7"
msgid "So cassa bahvābādho; "
msgstr "If he’s unhealthy, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.8"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ appābādhena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya. "
msgstr "he wouldn’t achieve what he could with good health. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.9"
msgid "So cassa saṭho māyāvī; "
msgstr "If he’s devious or deceitful, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.10"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ asaṭhena amāyāvinā pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya. "
msgstr "he wouldn’t achieve what he could with honesty and integrity. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.11"
msgid "So cassa kusīto; "
msgstr "If he’s lazy, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.12"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ āraddhavīriyena pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya. "
msgstr "he wouldn’t achieve what he could with energy. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.13"
msgid "So cassa duppañño; "
msgstr "If he’s stupid, "

msgctxt "mn85:56.14"
msgid "yāvatakaṃ paññavatā pattabbaṃ taṃ na sampāpuṇeyya. "
msgstr "he wouldn’t achieve what he could with wisdom. "

msgctxt "mn85:56.15"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññasi, rājakumāra, "
msgstr "What do you think, prince? "

msgctxt "mn85:56.16"
msgid "api nu so puriso tava santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyyā”ti? "
msgstr "Could that man still train under you in the art of wielding a hooked goad while riding an elephant?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn85:56.17"
msgid "“Ekamekenāpi, bhante, aṅgena samannāgato so puriso na mama santike hatthārūḷhaṃ aṅkusagayhaṃ sippaṃ sikkheyya, ko pana vādo pañcahaṅgehī”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, if he had even a single one of these factors he couldn’t train under me, let alone all five.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
